	  <h2 class="display-4">The Brains of the Operation</h2>
	  <p>Members of software work in groups to tackle computer vision and localization challenges, and develop a strategy to complete our mission in the IARC.
		  To do this, we work closely with graduate students and leverage advanced algorithms.
		  The most challenging component of our competition is computer vision based localization.
		  We detect lines and ground robots using input from five on-board RGBD cameras using our customized detection algorithms.
		  The results are passed onto a highly sophisticated model that fuses input from the on-board inertial measurement unit (IMU) and computer vision results to predict the location of our vehicle in real time.
		  We also benchmark various state-of-the-art object tracking algorithms and adapt the one best suited for our mission.
		  Finally, we execute a mission strategy using knowledge of our current state of the vehicle and ground robots inside the competition arena.</p>
