	  <h2 class="display-4">The Infrastructure of Intelligent Flight</h2>
	  <p>The Software Infrastructure team writes the software that coordinates the execution of navigation software, simulates the competition, and communicates with the physical hardware. We allow various navigation software components to communicate with each other. In addition, we write software which provides a publish/subscribe interface to the physical hardware, allowing navigation software components to subscribe to sensor updates or publish control input. To simulate the competition, we can swap out the hardware interface software with simulator software that exposes the same interface to the navigation software components, but instead of talking to hardware, talks to a simulated quadcopter in a simulated field. The Software Infrastructure team writes both embedded, bare metal software running on an ARM microcontroller, low level Linux Software, and Linux applications.</p>
